<section id="verify" class="section-block">
	<h2>2. Verify checksum (optional)</h2>
	<p>Validate file integrity by comparing SHA-256 checksums.</p>
	<ol>
		<li>Open <code>Terminal</code>.</li>
		<li>Run: <code>shasum -a 256 VoiceTel-3.5.6-arm64.dmg</code> (or whichever file you downloaded).</li>
		<li>Compare the output with the value listed above.</li>
	</ol>
</section>

<section id="install" class="section-block">
	<h2>3. Install</h2>
	<ol>
		<li>Open the downloaded <strong>.dmg</strong>.</li>
		<li>Drag <strong>VoiceTel Phone.app</strong> to the <strong>Applications</strong> folder. Eject the disk image when finished.</li>
		<li>If macOS warns that the app is from the Internet on first launch, go to <em>System Settings &rarr; Privacy &amp; Security</em>, scroll to the security message for VoiceTel Phone, and click <em>Open Anyway</em>.</li>
	</ol>
</section>

<section id="firstlaunch" class="section-block">
	<h2>4. First launch</h2>
	<ol>
		<li>Open <strong>VoiceTel Phone</strong> from Applications.</li>
		<li>Allow microphone access when prompted. If you missed the prompt, go to <em>System Settings &rarr; Privacy &amp; Security &rarr; Microphone</em> and enable access for <em>VoiceTel Phone</em>.</li>
		<li>Enter your VoiceTel SIP credentials (username, password, display name) as provisioned in the customer portal.</li>
	</ol>
</section>

<section id="faq" class="section-block faq-block">
	<h2>FAQ</h2>
	<details class="faq-item">
		<summary>How do I uninstall VoiceTel Phone?</summary>
		<p>Quit the app, open <em>Applications</em>, and drag <strong>VoiceTel Phone.app</strong> to the Trash.</p>
	</details>
	<details class="faq-item">
		<summary>The app won't open after installation</summary>
		<p>Right-click the app and choose <em>Open</em> to bypass Gatekeeper. You can also go to <em>System Settings &rarr; Privacy &amp; Security</em> and click <em>Open Anyway</em>.</p>
	</details>
	<details class="faq-item">
		<summary>The microphone isn't working</summary>
		<p>Ensure VoiceTel Phone has permission under <em>System Settings &rarr; Privacy &amp; Security &rarr; Microphone</em>. Also check <em>System Settings &rarr; Sound</em> for the correct input device.</p>
	</details>
	<details class="faq-item">
		<summary>Can I pre-configure the app for my users?</summary>
		<p>Yes. Place <code>voicetel.json</code> under <code>~/Library/Application Support/VoiceTelPhone/</code> for user-level deployment, or <code>/Library/Application Support/VoiceTelPhone/</code> for system-wide deployment.</p>
	</details>
</section>

